-- European Leaders Said to Plan Call Today Before G-8 Summit
-- B y   J a m e s   H e r t l i n g
-- 2012-05-17T10:13:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/european-leaders-said-to-plan-call-today-before-g-8-summit.html
European leaders heading to a Group
of Eight summit that starts tomorrow outside Washington plan to
convene a conference call today, according to two officials from
G-8 countries.  Germany’s Angela Merkel, France’s  Francois Hollande ,
Italy’s Mario Monti, and Britain’s David Cameron, along with
European Union leaders Herman Van Rompuy and Jose Barroso will
talk together today, said the officials, who declined to be
identified, citing government policy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Hertling in Paris at 
